ce\", \"score\": 0.9927190842518033, \"rank\": 0.00720992429739183, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"joy\", \"from\": 1225, \"to\": 1228}, {\"ngram\": \"emulation\", \"from\": 1230, \"to\": 1239}, {\"ngram\": \"movement\", \"from\": 1241, \"to\": 1249}, {\"ngram\": \"excitement\", \"from\": 1251, \"to\": 1261}, {\"ngram\": \"sparkle\", \"from\": 1266, \"to\": 1273}, {\"ngram\": \"not only those famous philosophical values\", \"from\": 1279, \"to\": 1321}, {\"ngram\": \"a bit too much self-assurance\", \"from\": 1358, \"to\": 1387}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Historian and author Patrick Boucheron, another member of the creative team drafted in by Jolly, said the Paris ceremony would be nothing like the spectacular parade seen at the Beijing Olympics.\", \"from\": 1391, \"to\": 1586, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1412, \"end\": 1419, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Star\", \"score\": 0.9960606259450042, \"rank\": 0.0038743618159491323, \"text\": \"Patrick\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Star\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Star\"}, {\"begin\": 1420, \"end\": 1429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boucheron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Boucheron\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boucheron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boucheron\"}, {\"begin\": 1497, \"end\": 1502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999994989724547, \"rank\": 5.010277733381466e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Historian\", \"from\": 1391, \"to\": 1400}, {\"ngram\": \"author\", \"from\": 1405, \"to\": 1411}, {\"ngram\": \"another member\", \"from\": 1431, \"to\": 1445}, {\"ngram\": \"the creative team\", \"from\": 1449, \"to\": 1466}, {\"ngram\": \"Jolly\", \"from\": 1481, \"to\": 1486}, {\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 1521, \"to\": 1528}, {\"ngram\": \"the spectacular parade\", \"from\": 1534, \"to\": 1556}, {\"ngram\": \"the Beijing Olympics\", \"from\": 1565, \"to\": 1585}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The opening ceremony in Beijing in 2008 was exactly what we did not want to do: a history lesson addressed to the world from the host country, an ode to grandeur and a display of power,\\\" he told the newspaper.\", \"from\": 1588, \"to\": 1798, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1613, \"end\": 1620, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beijing\", \"score\": 0.892487983544646, \"rank\": 0.10207744400212464, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beijing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beijing\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1589, \"to\": 1609}, {\"ngram\": \"exactly what\", \"from\": 1633, \"to\": 1645}, {\"ngram\": \"a history lesson\", \"from\": 1669, \"to\": 1685}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1699, \"to\": 1708}, {\"ngram\": \"the host country\", \"from\": 1714, \"to\": 1730}, {\"ngram\": \"an ode\", \"from\": 1732, \"to\": 1738}, {\"ngram\": \"a display\", \"from\": 1755, \"to\": 1764}, {\"ngram\": \"power\", \"from\": 1768, \"to\": 1773}, {\"ngram\": \"the newspaper\", \"from\": 1784, \"to\": 1797}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris event would \\\"speak of the world to France and of France to the world\\\" while being \\\"the opposite of a virile, heroic story\\\".\", \"from\": 1800, \"to\": 1933, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1804, \"end\": 1809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999994989724547, \"rank\": 5.010277733381466e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedi